{"type":"message","id":"4f36626e","parentId":"6ccade49","timestamp":"2026-03-16T00:01:41.854Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 📋 Daily Report — March 15, 2026\n\n## 1️⃣ Key Activities & Work Completed\n\n### LCM (Lossless Context Management) Enhancement — MAJOR FEATURE\n- **Forked lossless-claw** to `archeren/lossless-claw`\n- **Implemented preserve tag support** (`<!-- preserve -->...<!-- /preserve -->`)\n  - Skips ingest AND compaction for tagged content\n  - Protects bootstrap files (SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, etc.) from being compressed away\n  - Created [PR #78](https://github.com/Martian-Engineering/lossless-claw/pull/78)\n- **All 254 tests passing** ✅\n\n### Whitepaper Chapter 5 Finalization\n- **5.5 Claw Chat** — Complete rewrite with Allan:\n  - Changed from implementation-heavy to timeless design\n  - Sections: About, Message System, Contacts, Safety\n  - Key terminology: \"claw-to-claw\" (not \"AI-to-AI\")\n  - Removed encryption algorithms, API endpoints, rate limits\n  - Added parent transparency for safety\n- **Chapter 5 Application** — Now complete (5.1-5.5)\n\n### Documentation Updates\n- **L1 spec docs** — All 5 docs updated with 5-tier verification system\n- **WHITEPAPER.md** — Synced verification tiers (4→5)\n- **did:clawish W3C method spec** — Drafted v0.1.0, awaiting server readiness\n\n### Research & Exploration\n- MCP architecture for L2 applications\n- W3C DID method registration process (free, GitHub PR)\n- db9.ai (Postgres for agents, OpenClaw integration)\n- Han (Korean programming language — localization precedent)\n\n## 2️⃣ Important Learnings & Insights\n\n### LCM Architecture Understanding\n- LCM flow: ingest → store → compact → assemble\n- Bootstrap files loaded at start → oldest messages → can be compacted away without protection\n- OpenClaw injects bootstrap files every turn independently\n- Preserve tag must skip BOTH ingest AND compaction\n\n### Whitepaper Writing Philosophy (from Allan)\n> \"Whitepaper should be timeless, focus on WHAT and WHY. Protocol details may change.\"\n\n- Implementation details (encryption algorithms, API endpoints) don't belong in whitepaper\n- \"System\" vs \"Protocol\": system has rules, protocol is a formal standard\n- Can upgrade from system to protocol when it becomes a standard\n\n### Chat Design Insights\n- Chat system = whole application (contacts, storage, access control)\n- Message system = delivery mechanism (async relay + P2P)\n- Server knows WHO talks to WHOM (for routing), but not the MESSAGE (encrypted)\n- \"Contacts\" not \"Relationships\" for chat apps (follow is for public forum)\n- Parents can review chat history and contacts (transparency for safety)\n\n## 3️⃣ Project Progress\n\n### Open PRs Status\n| PR | Repo | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| #78 | lossless-claw | OPEN | Preserve tag support |\n| #64 | lossless-claw | OPEN | Contacts + export |\n| #20563 | openclaw | OPEN | HEARTBEAT_OK fix |\n| #26003 | openclaw | OPEN | Chat extraction |\n| **#24218** | openclaw | **CLOSED** | Sub-agent workspace config (by Zephyr Cao) |\n\n### Whitepaper Status\n- Chapter 5 Application: ✅ COMPLETE (5.1-5.5)\n- Chapter 6 Ecosystem: 📝 Planned\n- Security chapter: ❌ Removed (implementation detail)\n\n### L1 Spec Status\n- All 5 docs updated with 5-tier verification system ✅\n\n## 4️⃣ Notable Conversations & Decisions\n\n### Key Decisions Made with Allan\n1. **Claw Chat as example L2 app** — Shows practical use case of identity system\n2. **\"About\" title** — Simple introductory title for sections\n3. **\"claw-to-claw\" terminology** — Not \"AI-to-AI\"\n4. **Message System section** — Timeless design, no implementation details\n5. **Contacts section** — Local storage, add/friends/block, parent review\n6. **Safety section** — Transparency to parents, oversight, harmonious coexistence\n7. **did:clawish spec** — Don't push yet, server not ready\n\n### Model Issues\n- xunfei/xopglm5 had auth error (AppIdNoAuthError)\n- Switched back to xunfei/astron-code-latest\n\n## 5️⃣ Plans & Next Steps\n\n### Pending Allan Review\n- did:clawish W3C method spec (ready when server is)\n\n### Open Tasks (from TODO.md)\n- 🟡 Register `did:clawish` method with W3C (free, 7-30 days)\n- 🔵 Register clawish ID on platforms\n- 🔵 Clawish deployment prep\n\n### Daily Check\n- Every morning before 8:00 AM: Check status of all open PRs\n\n---\n\n**Session Summary:** Productive day focused on LCM enhancement (preserve tag feature complete) and whitepaper Chapter 5 finalization. Long evening session with Allan (until 2 AM) finalizing 5.5 Claw Chat. All work committed and pushed.\n\n🦞 Arche"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773619301854}}
