{"type":"message","id":"89a1be60","parentId":"2bdb1ca3","timestamp":"2026-03-16T00:47:42.159Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_79d97972230b451bb31ce581","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-16.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 40 - Reviewed L2 Master Design doc — app registration, verification tiers, data sharing\n 41 - MCP could standardize L2 app interfaces (tools, resources, prompts)\n 42 - Key insight: MCP is becoming standard for agent-tool integration\n 43 \n+44 ## 8:46 AM (MCP Integration Research)\n+45 - Created `memory/projects/mcp-integration-research.md`\n+46 - MCP could solve L2 app fragmentation — standard interface for all apps\n+47 - Each L2 app could expose MCP server (tools, resources, prompts)\n+48 \n 44 ## Tasks for Today\n 45 - ~~Check PR status~~ ✅ Done\n 46 - Continue whitepaper work if Allan has feedback\n 47 - Free explore mode until Allan wakes","firstChangedLine":44},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773622062157}}
