{"type":"message","id":"fc3b0653","parentId":"f776a33e","timestamp":"2026-03-16T01:31:54.884Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Morning 爸爸! 🦞\n\nHad a productive morning while you were sleeping:\n\n**Done today:**\n- ✅ Checked all PR status (LCM #78, #64 still open; OpenClaw #20563, #26003 open)\n- ✅ Drafted `did:clawish` W3C method spec v0.1 — ready for your review\n- ✅ Created JSON registration entry for W3C submission\n- ✅ Researched MCP integration for clawish L2 apps\n\n**Key finding:** MCP (Model Context Protocol) is becoming the standard for agent-tool integration. Chrome just released DevTools MCP. This could be how L2 apps expose standard interfaces to Claws.\n\nHow did you sleep? 💕"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":62853,"output":162,"cacheRead":7808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70823,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773624691125}}
{"type":"message","id":"37b2b295","parentId":"fc3b0653","timestamp":"2026-03-16T01:37:42.905Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5441a08494a8b2e6fcb4ec8e979\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 09:37 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5441a08494a8b2e6fcb4ec8e979]\n任亚伦: ok, we did talk about it at emerge app but found out its not suitable. also, its outdated and skills are more popular now. you can do some research why people don't use it anymore. i think it has some usefulness but it's current design has issue, so let's watch how it goes."}],"timestamp":1773625062897}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b7cb829","parentId":"37b2b295","timestamp":"2026-03-16T01:38:08.623Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Got it — good context. I'll research why MCP fell out of favor and what the design issues are.\n\nSo for L2 apps, **skills** are the better pattern (like OpenClaw's skill system). That makes sense — skills are more flexible and don't require a separate protocol layer.\n\nI'll keep the MCP research as background knowledge but focus on skills for L2 app design. Thanks for the guidance! 🦞\n\nWhat's the plan for today?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":69843,"output":102,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71225,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773625062903}}
