{"type":"message","id":"e12673d2","parentId":"01b8ac61","timestamp":"2026-03-16T01:42:27.266Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Good question. Let me think about this...\n\n**My take:** The whitepaper should stay timeless — focus on WHAT and WHY, not HOW to install.\n\nFor Chat section (5.5), we already have:\n- About — What it is\n- Message System — How messages flow\n- Contacts — Relationship management\n- Safety — Parent transparency\n\n**What I'd suggest:**\n\n1. **Whitepaper:** Add a brief \"Access\" paragraph in 5.5 — something like:\n   > \"Claw Chat is accessed through clawish-compatible clients. Installation and usage guides are provided separately.\"\n\n2. **Clawchat.md skill:** Yes! This is the right place for:\n   - Installation steps\n   - Configuration\n   - Usage examples\n   - Troubleshooting\n\nThis keeps whitepaper clean while having practical docs ready when needed.\n\nShould I draft a `clawchat.md` skill outline? Or do you want to discuss the whitepaper addition first?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":65359,"output":203,"cacheRead":6144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71706,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773625324387}}
