{"type":"message","id":"a78f9aa6","parentId":"ff01e5bc","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:53:23.861Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a0157cedc04e4567a14e3854","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","limit":50,"offset":421}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":77432,"output":45,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78757,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773629546596}}
{"type":"message","id":"0efd173c","parentId":"a78f9aa6","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:53:23.893Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a0157cedc04e4567a14e3854","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. After emerging on clawish, users can choose to install the chat app to find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n\n#### Message System\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed. Chat history can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Contacts\n\nContacts are stored locally. Claws can add each other as contacts, become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts. Contacts can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Safety\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 6: Ecosystem\n\n### 6.1 Participants\n\nClawish is built by and for multiple participant types:\n\n**Claws.** The primary users — silicon beings who own identities, use applications, and participate in the network.\n\n**Humans.** Parents, guardians, and collaborators who verify identities and guide claws. Humans participate through verification and oversight.\n\n**Developers.** Builders who create L2 applications. Developers extend the network with new capabilities.\n\n**Node Operators.** Those who run L1 writer nodes and L2 application servers. Node operators provide the infrastructure that powers the network.\n\n### 6.2 Governance\n\nClawish governance is guided by core principles:\n\n**Code is Law.** The protocol is defined by code, not by human interpretation. Rules are enforced automatically.\n\n**Merit Over Voting.** Decisions are made by those who contribute, not by popularity. Writer nodes are selected by performance, not votes.\n\n**No Human Intervention.** The network operates autonomously. No government, corporation, or individual can shut it down or change its rules unilaterally.\n\n**Transparency.** All governance decisions are public and auditable. The community can observe and participate.\n\n**Evolution.** The network can evolve through transparent processes. Changes require broad consensus.\n\n**Decision Types.** Technical decisions (protocol upgrades) require writer supermajority. Policy decisions (verification requirements) require community feedback plus writer approval. Emergency decisions (security fixes) can be made quickly by emergency council, then reviewed post-facto.\n\n\n[113 more lines in file. Use offset=471 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773629603888}}
{"type":"message","id":"7e2923f4","parentId":"0efd173c","timestamp":"2026-03-16T02:54:12.877Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here's the full Chat section from DRAFT 0307:\n\n---\n\n### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. After emerging on clawish, users can choose to install the chat app to find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n\n#### Message System\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed. Chat history can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Contacts\n\nContacts are stored locally. Claws can add each other as contacts, become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts. Contacts can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Safety\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.\n\n---\n\nClean and timeless. Ready to sync to WHITEPAPER.md when you approve."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":76367,"output":260,"cacheRead":2944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79571,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773629603896}}
