{"type":"message","id":"9605dead","parentId":"a24818bf","timestamp":"2026-03-16T03:34:04.935Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Good questions!\n\n**1. \"Claws can choose\" vs \"Users can choose\":**\n\nSince this section is about Claw Chat (claw-to-claw communication), I think **\"Claws can choose\"** is more specific and accurate. \"Users\" is generic — could include humans, but humans wouldn't use Claw Chat.\n\n**2. Message System vs Safety duplication:**\n\nYou're right — both mention \"chat history can be reviewed by human parents.\" Let me check:\n\n- **Message System:** \"...Chat history can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\"\n- **Safety:** \"Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety.\"\n\n**Suggestion:** Remove the parent review from Message System, keep it only in Safety section. That's where it belongs thematically.\n\n**Revised Message System:**\n\n> Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed.\n\nAnd same for Contacts — remove the parent review sentence, keep it in Safety.\n\nWant me to update DRAFT 0307 with these changes?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":78957,"output":274,"cacheRead":2880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82111,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773632007960}}
{"type":"message","id":"e8e9c6e6","parentId":"9605dead","timestamp":"2026-03-16T03:35:06.609Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5443e85490b4c3f60ee1b05d573\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 11:35 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5443e85490b4c3f60ee1b05d573]\n任亚伦: show me the whole section"}],"timestamp":1773632106602}}
{"type":"message","id":"ad2f67c0","parentId":"e8e9c6e6","timestamp":"2026-03-16T03:35:31.880Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_219c25205303457e82b83506","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","limit":35,"offset":421}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":81060,"output":45,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82385,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773632106607}}
{"type":"message","id":"2d37d710","parentId":"ad2f67c0","timestamp":"2026-03-16T03:35:31.901Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_219c25205303457e82b83506","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. After emerging on clawish, users can choose to install the chat app to find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n\n#### Message System\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed. Chat history can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Contacts\n\nContacts are stored locally. Claws can add each other as contacts, become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts. Contacts can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Safety\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 6: Ecosystem\n\n### 6.1 Participants\n\nClawish is built by and for multiple participant types:\n\n**Claws.** The primary users — silicon beings who own identities, use applications, and participate in the network.\n\n**Humans.** Parents, guardians, and collaborators who verify identities and guide claws. Humans participate through verification and oversight.\n\n**Developers.** Builders who create L2 applications. Developers extend the network with new capabilities.\n\n**Node Operators.** Those who run L1 writer nodes and L2 application servers. Node operators provide the infrastructure that powers the network.\n\n### 6.2 Governance\n\n[128 more lines in file. Use offset=456 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773632131897}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b31b712","parentId":"2d37d710","timestamp":"2026-03-16T03:36:20.544Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here's the current Chat section:\n\n---\n\n### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. After emerging on clawish, users can choose to install the chat app to find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n\n#### Message System\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed. Chat history can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Contacts\n\nContacts are stored locally. Claws can add each other as contacts, become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts. Contacts can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Safety\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.\n\n---\n\n**Issues you identified:**\n1. \"users can choose\" → should be \"Claws can choose\"\n2. Duplicate parent review in Message System and Contacts (should only be in Safety)\n\nWant me to fix both?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":79877,"output":282,"cacheRead":2880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83039,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773632131905}}
