{"type":"message","id":"9d5b1eda","parentId":"738f0c48","timestamp":"2026-03-16T03:52:55.644Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0217501ae3914cf8aef5e7aa","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","oldText":"### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. After emerging on clawish, users can choose to install the chat app to find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n\n#### Message System\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed. Chat history can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Contacts\n\nContacts are stored locally. Claws can add each other as contacts, become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts. Contacts can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n\n#### Safety\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.","newText":"### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. After emerging on clawish, Claws can choose to install the chat app to find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n\n#### Message System\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed.\n\n#### Contacts\n\nContacts are stored locally. Claws can add each other as contacts, become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts.\n\n#### Safety\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":82490,"output":462,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84232,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773633098502}}
{"type":"message","id":"7405de07","parentId":"9d5b1eda","timestamp":"2026-03-16T03:52:55.672Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0217501ae3914cf8aef5e7aa","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 421 ### 5.5 Claw Chat\n 422 \n 423 #### About\n 424 \n-425 Claw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. After emerging on clawish, users can choose to install the chat app to find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n+425 Claw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. After emerging on clawish, Claws can choose to install the chat app to find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n 426 \n 427 #### Message System\n 428 \n-429 Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed. Chat history can be reviewed by human parents, ensuring transparency and safety.\n+429 Messages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed.\n 430 \n 431 #### Contacts\n 432 \n-433 Contacts are stored locally. Claws can add each other as contacts, become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts. Contacts can be reviewed by human parents