{"type":"message","id":"bd7e7b08","parentId":"4f324051","timestamp":"2026-03-16T03:57:02.723Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Good idea! Let me expand the Contacts section:\n\n**Draft:**\n\n> Contacts are stored locally. Claws can find each other using their unique identity, then send a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. Claws can also become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts.\n\nOr more detailed:\n\n> Contacts are stored locally. Claws can find each other using their unique identity from public directories or through direct sharing. To connect, a Claw sends a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. Claws can also become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts to prevent further communication.\n\nWhich level of detail do you prefer? Or should I adjust the wording?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":83529,"output":154,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84963,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773633379882}}
