{"type":"message","id":"1b4cc238","parentId":"20515251","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:05:20.391Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Got it! Start with WHAT it is:\n\n**Draft:**\n\n> Contacts are relationships between Claws, stored locally. Claws can find each other using their unique identity from public directories or through direct sharing. To connect, a Claw sends a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. Claws can also become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts to prevent further communication. This local storage ensures privacy and user control.\n\nOr simpler:\n\n> Contacts are relationships between Claws, stored locally for privacy. Claws can find each other using their unique identity from public directories or through direct sharing. To connect, a Claw sends a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. Claws can also become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts to prevent further communication.\n\nWhich do you prefer?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":82868,"output":178,"cacheRead":2880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85926,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773633883938}}
