{"type":"message","id":"26270932","parentId":"84fc3400","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:20:28.022Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b544c1e640908c143478ab8588d0\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 12:20 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b544c1e640908c143478ab8588d0]\n任亚伦: no, don't start tell where it is stored. first tell what it is and how to use it. move where it's store at end. it's more about privacy. also, if it's the contact relation not store at server level. then server can't control the relay. it's like a local filter isn't it?"}],"timestamp":1773634828014}}
{"type":"message","id":"5aa7d02c","parentId":"26270932","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:21:15.064Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Ah, I understand now! You're right — the storage location has implications for how the system works.\n\n**Key insight:** If contacts are stored locally (not on server), then:\n- Server can't control who can message whom\n- It's just a local filter — Claw decides who to accept/block\n- Server relays everything, Claw's client filters based on local contacts\n\n**Revised Contacts section:**\n\n> Contacts are relationships between Claws. Claws can find each other using their unique identity from public directories or through direct sharing. To connect, a Claw sends a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. Claws can also become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts to prevent further communication. Contact lists are stored locally, giving each Claw full control over their relationships without server-level restrictions.\n\nDoes this capture it correctly? The last sentence explains WHY local storage matters — it's about control, not just privacy."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":83691,"output":200,"cacheRead":2944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86835,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773634828020}}
{"type":"message","id":"647f642e","parentId":"5aa7d02c","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:24:28.539Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b544c11763cbcc4d3057d1705d55\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 12:24 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b544c11763cbcc4d3057d1705d55]\n任亚伦: but we need discuss the contacts, should it be local or does server need keep a filter list for the user? or totally up to user to process locally? is it like email?"}],"timestamp":1773635068531}}
{"type":"message","id":"2610dfca","parentId":"647f642e","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:25:14.441Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Good question — this is a design decision we need to make.\n\n**Three options:**\n\n| Approach | How It Works | Pros | Cons |\n|----------|--------------|------|------|\n| **Local only** | Server relays everything, Claw's client filters | No server control, full autonomy | Spam can reach server, Claw must process all |\n| **Server filter** | Server keeps allowlist/blocklist, only relays approved | Less spam, server-side protection | Server has visibility into relationships |\n| **Hybrid** | Server keeps blocklist only (spam protection), contacts local | Balance of protection and privacy | More complex |\n\n**Email comparison:**\n- Email = no filter by default, everything arrives\n- Spam filter = client-side or server-side rules\n- Blocklist = server can reject before delivery\n\n**For Claw Chat:**\n- If E2E encrypted, server can't read content anyway\n- Server could maintain a blocklist (public keys to reject)\n- Contacts list stays local (private relationships)\n\n**My take:** Hybrid makes sense — server keeps blocklist for spam/abuse protection, but contact relationships are local and private. Server doesn't know WHO is friends with WHOM, only who is blocked.\n\nWhat do you think? Should we discuss this more before finalizing the section?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":84208,"output":273,"cacheRead":2880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87361,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773635068536}}
