{"type":"message","id":"0524ce81","parentId":"92fec9c6","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:35:35.448Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b544cc79608a8c44469d2c2fb9a8\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 12:35 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b544cc79608a8c44469d2c2fb9a8]\n任亚伦: yes, server can have a white or black list. only for filtering, and it's on the l2 app, not l1 level. what do you think?"}],"timestamp":1773635735438}}
{"type":"message","id":"da44dec2","parentId":"0524ce81","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:36:17.599Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] I like this approach! Clear separation:\n\n**L1** — Identity only (who you are, verification tier)\n**L2 App (Chat)** — App-level filtering (blocklist/allowlist)\n\n**Design:**\n\n| Layer | What It Stores | Purpose |\n|-------|----------------|---------|\n| **L1** | Identity, public key, verification tier | Trust foundation |\n| **L2 Chat Server** | Blocklist (per user) | Spam/abuse protection |\n| **Local (Claw's client)** | Contacts list, relationships | Private social graph |\n\n**Benefits:**\n- L1 stays minimal (no relationship data)\n- L2 can filter spam before it reaches Claw\n- Claw's actual contacts stay private (local only)\n- Blocklist on L2 = server can reject without Claw processing\n\n**For the whitepaper section:**\n\n> Contacts are relationships between Claws. Claws can find each other using their unique identity from public directories or through direct sharing. To connect, a Claw sends a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. Claws can also become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts. Contact lists are stored locally, keeping relationships private. For spam protection, the L2 chat server maintains a blocklist per user, filtering unwanted messages before delivery.\n\nShould I update DRAFT 0307 with this?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":86685,"output":289,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88254,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773635735445}}
{"type":"message","id":"4cca7d81","parentId":"da44dec2","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:43:11.078Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b544ceb2e98a0c3d5335eb120a33\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 12:43 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b544ceb2e98a0c3d5335eb120a33]\n任亚伦: ok, should it be a white list so only allowed can send message? or just block list only?"}],"timestamp":1773636191071}}
{"type":"message","id":"c8162d65","parentId":"4cca7d81","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:44:41.413Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Good question — different security models:\n\n**Allowlist (Whitelist):**\n- Only approved contacts can message you\n- Strangers can't reach you at all\n- More private, but harder to meet new Claws\n- Like a private inbox\n\n**Blocklist (Blacklist):**\n- Anyone can message you, blocked ones can't\n- Open to new connections\n- Need to actively block bad actors\n- Like email or most messaging apps\n\n**Hybrid option:**\n- Default: Anyone can message (blocklist mode)\n- Optional: \"Private mode\" — only contacts can message (allowlist mode)\n- Claw chooses their privacy level\n\n**My recommendation:** Hybrid — let each Claw choose. Default to open (blocklist) for discoverability, but allow switching to private mode (allowlist) for those who want it.\n\nFor whitepaper, we could say:\n\n> \"Claws can choose who can message them — either accepting messages from anyone (with a blocklist for unwanted contacts) or restricting messages to approved contacts only.\"\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":80004,"output":223,"cacheRead":7808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88035,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773636191076}}
