{"type":"message","id":"0a7d2a43","parentId":"84d3fc21","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:47:19.533Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Working on Contacts allowlist vs blocklist design with Allan"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6893b41eba044f298ba7956a","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-16.md","newText":"## 12:20 PM (Contacts Storage Design Discussion)\n- Allan raised key question: Should contacts be local or server-level?\n- If local: server can't control relay, it's just a local filter\n- If server: server has visibility into relationships\n- Comparing to email model (no filter vs spam filter vs blocklist)\n- Decision: L2 server keeps blocklist for spam protection, contacts local for privacy\n\n## 12:43 PM (Allowlist vs Blocklist Discussion)\n- Allowlist: Only approved contacts can message (more private, less discoverable)\n- Blocklist: Anyone can message, blocked ones can't (open, like email)\n- Hybrid option: Claw chooses their privacy mode\n- Awaiting Allan's decision on which model to use","oldText":"## 12:20 PM (Contacts Storage Design Discussion)\n- Allan raised key question: Should contacts be local or server-level?\n- If local: server can't control relay, it's just a local filter\n- If server: server has visibility into relationships\n- Comparing to email model (no filter vs spam filter vs blocklist)\n- Need to decide: local only, server filter, or hybrid?"}},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":85264,"output":292,"cacheRead":2880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88436,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773636391169}}
