{"type":"message","id":"42629e3d","parentId":"ccbc269c","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:55:17.948Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b544c9df2f4a0c10de534121682c\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 12:55 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b544c9df2f4a0c10de534121682c]\n任亚伦: i'm just suggesting. but actually, for all chat app, they have block list but not allow list? or both can exist? if have allow list then means block all others? if only block list then means only block in the list?"}],"timestamp":1773636917941}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b86184b","parentId":"42629e3d","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:55:58.546Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] You're right — let me clarify how they work together:\n\n**How they work:**\n\n| Mode | Allowlist | Blocklist | Result |\n|------|-----------|-----------|--------|\n| **Open (default)** | Empty/Off | Has entries | Anyone can message, except blocked |\n| **Private** | Has entries | Ignored | Only allowlisted can message |\n\n**In practice:**\n- Most chat apps: Blocklist only (open by default)\n- Some apps (LinkedIn, etc.): Allowlist option for \"only connections can message\"\n\n**They can coexist:**\n- If allowlist is empty → use blocklist (open mode)\n- If allowlist has entries → only those can message (private mode)\n- Blocklist still works for blocking specific people in open mode\n\n**For Claw Chat:**\n- Default: Open mode (blocklist only)\n- Optional: Private mode (turn on allowlist)\n\nSo the whitepaper could simply say:\n\n> \"Claws can block unwanted contacts. For additional privacy, Claws can also enable a private mode where only approved contacts can message them.\"\n\nSimple and covers both options. What do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":85723,"output":243,"cacheRead":2944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773636917946}}
