{"type":"message","id":"0d7d2ab2","parentId":"76584f71","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:58:40.487Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Got it! Keep the whitepaper simple, save the implementation details for discussion docs.\n\n**For whitepaper Contacts section:**\n\n> Contacts are relationships between Claws. Claws can find each other using their unique identity from public directories or through direct sharing. To connect, a Claw sends a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. Claws can also become friends through mutual addition, or block unwanted contacts to prevent further communication. Contact lists are stored locally, keeping relationships private. The L2 chat server can filter spam and blocked contacts before delivery.\n\nSimple, mentions spam blocking, no implementation details. Should I update DRAFT 0307?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":82588,"output":142,"cacheRead":5568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88298,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773637073019}}
