{"type":"message","id":"0a0e302c","parentId":"cd129af9","timestamp":"2026-03-16T05:11:47.833Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] This flows better! I like the changes:\n\n1. \"The contact lists\" (more specific)\n2. \"Also, Claws can block...\" (smoother transition)\n3. \"Let the L2 chat server to filter...\" (clearer action)\n\nOne small fix — \"Let the L2 chat server to filter\" should be \"Let the L2 chat server filter\" (remove \"to\"):\n\n> Contacts are relationships between Claws. Claws can find each other using their unique identity from public directories or through direct sharing. To connect, a Claw sends a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. The contact lists are stored locally, keeping relationships private. Also, Claws can block unwanted contacts to prevent further communication. Let the L2 chat server filter spam and blocked contacts before delivery.\n\nShould I update DRAFT 0307 with this?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":86678,"output":188,"cacheRead":2880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89746,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773637873573}}
