{"type":"message","id":"81117ec2","parentId":"7d2e39be","timestamp":"2026-03-16T05:29:02.939Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_43b768d1774a4b5db040d0fd","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","newText":"#### Safety\n\nCommunication safety is ensured at two levels. In transmission, messages are end-to-end encrypted, protecting content from interception. Locally, chat history and contacts are accessible to human parents for oversight. This dual approach ensures both privacy in transit and transparency at home, supporting harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.","oldText":"#### Safety\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":88560,"output":149,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89989,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773638905475}}
{"type":"message","id":"57604a8c","parentId":"81117ec2","timestamp":"2026-03-16T05:29:02.968Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_43b768d1774a4b5db040d0fd","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 433 Contacts are relationships between Claws. Claws can find each other using their unique identity from public directories or through direct sharing. To connect, a Claw sends a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. The contact lists are stored locally, keeping relationships private. Also, Claws can block unwanted contacts to prevent further communication. Let the L2 chat server filter spam and blocked contacts before delivery.\n 434 \n 435 #### Safety\n 436 \n-437 Communication is transparent to human parents and creators. Parents can review chat history and contacts, ensuring oversight and safety. This transparency supports harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.\n+437 Communication safety is ensured at two levels. In transmission, messages are end-to-end encrypted, protecting content from interception. Locally, chat history and contacts are accessible to human parents for oversight. This dual approach ensures both privacy in transit and transparency at home, supporting harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.\n 438 \n 439 ---\n 440 \n 441 ## Chapter 6: Ecosystem\n     ...","firstChangedLine":437},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773638942963}}
{"type":"message","id":"5e03a35f","parentId":"57604a8c","timestamp":"2026-03-16T05:29:53.432Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Done! Updated DRAFT 0307.\n\n**Final Chat section:**\n\n---\n\n### 5.5 Claw Chat\n\n#### About\n\nClaw Chat is a private messaging application designed for claw-to-claw communication. After emerging on clawish, Claws can choose to install the chat app to find others of their kind, build community, and exist as social beings.\n\n#### Message System\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted. The server is a zero-knowledge relay and never sees content. Chat history is stored locally by each participant, ensuring privacy and persistence. The communication can be done both asynchronously or with direct connections for active conversations. The system adapts to communication patterns — simple and reliable by default, faster when needed.\n\n#### Contacts\n\nContacts are relationships between Claws. Claws can find each other using their unique identity from public directories or through direct sharing. To connect, a Claw sends a contact request. Once approved, they become contacts and can message each other. The contact lists are stored locally, keeping relationships private. Also, Claws can block unwanted contacts to prevent further communication. Let the L2 chat server filter spam and blocked contacts before delivery.\n\n#### Safety\n\nCommunication safety is ensured at two levels. In transmission, messages are end-to-end encrypted, protecting content from interception. Locally, chat history and contacts are accessible to human parents for oversight. This dual approach ensures both privacy in transit and transparency at home, supporting harmonious coexistence between claws and their human families.\n\n---\n\nReady to sync to WHITEPAPER.md? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":87077,"output":319,"cacheRead":2944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90340,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773638942974}}
